data.title: England men's Elite League squad named for November
meta_keywords: England men's elite league squad named
data.meta_description: Young Lions interim head coach Ben Futcher has picked his squad for their trip to Spain in November
data.text:
The England men’s Elite League squad has been named for November’s games with Italy and Germany.

New interim head coach Ben Futcher has selected a 23-player squad for the games, having taken over from Joe Edwards who left his role to become the new manager of Millwall. Futcher was previously assistant coach to Edwards for the first two camps of the season in September and October.

The Young Lions squad will meet up to begin their preparations next week before their first game against Italy at Doncaster Rovers FC on Thursday 16 November (7pm GMT).

They will then head to play Germany at the Jahnstadion Regensburg on Monday 20 November (5pm GMT) for their second game of the month.

Last month saw the newly-titled Elite League squad (formerly MU20s) suffer narrow defeats to both Romania and Portugal in their opening two games of the 2023-24 campaign.

Tickets for the match at the Eco-Power Stadium in Doncaster are on sale now.

The Squad

Goalkeepers: James Beadle (Oxford United, loan from Brighton & Hove Albion), Tommy Simkin (Solihull Moors, loan from Stoke City), Joe Whitworth (Crystal Palace)

Defenders: Nelson Abbey (Reading), Ryan Andrews (Watford), Luke Chambers (Liverpool), Ronnie Edwards (Peterborough United), Lewis Hall (Newcastle United (loan from Chelsea), Charlie Hughes (Wigan Athletic), Jadel Katongo (Peterborough United, loan from Manchester City)

Midfielders: Oliver Arblaster (Port Vale, loan from Sheffield United), Darko Gyabi (Leeds United), Archie Gray (Leeds United)**, Martial Godo (Wigan Athletic)* Charlie Webster (Heerenveen)*, Adam Wharton (Blackburn Rovers),

Forwards: Samuel Bell (Bristol City), Alfie Devine (Port Vale, loan from Tottenham Hotspur), Samuel Edozie (Southampton), Mateo Joseph (Leeds United), Jay Stansfield (Birmingham City, loan from Fulham)**, Dane Scarlett (Ipswich Town, loan from Tottenham Hotspur), Emran Soglo (Olympique Marseille)

* Replaces Daniel Gore (Manchester United), Tim Iroegbunam (Aston Villa) and Aaron Ramsey (Burnley) who are withdrawn injured

** Stansfield called into MU21s and Gray added from MU19s on Wednesday 15 November
